\exp(x) \exp(y) = \left(\sum_{m=0}^{\infty} \dfrac{x^m}{m!}\right)\left(\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \dfrac{y^n}{n!}\right) = \sum_{m=0}^{\infty}\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \dfrac{x^m}{m!}\dfrac{y^n}{n!}\\ = \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \sum_{m+n=k} \dfrac{x^m}{m!}\dfrac{y^n}{n!} = \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \sum_{n=0}^k \dfrac{x^{k-n}}{(k-n)!}\dfrac{y^n}{n!}
\dfrac{x^{k-n}}{(k-n)!}\dfrac{y^n}{n!} = \dfrac1{k!} \dbinom{k}n x^{k-n} y^n
\exp(x) \exp(y) = \underbrace{\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \dfrac1{k!} \sum_{n=0}^k \dbinom{k}n x^{k-n} y^n = \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \dfrac{(x+y)^k}{k!}}_{\text{Using binomial theorem}} = \exp(x+y)
\dbinom{x+y}k = \sum_{n=0}^k \dbinom{x}n \dbinom{y}{k-n} \,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\, (\star)
s(x+y) = \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \dbinom{x+y}k = \sum_{k=0}^{\infty}\sum_{n=0}^k \dbinom{x}n \dbinom{y}{k-n} = \sum_{k=0}^{\infty}\sum_{m+n=k} \dbinom{x}n \dbinom{y}{m}\\ = \sum_{m=0}^{\infty}\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \dbinom{x}n \dbinom{y}{m} = \left(\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \dbinom{x}n\right) \left(\sum_{m=0}^{\infty} \dbinom{y}{m} \right) = s(x) s(y)
